Actress Iyabo Ojo has reminisced on her life as a single mom 21 years after she left her ex-husband. She said she thought her life was over when she became a single mom and didn’t know she would come out fine. Sharing her experience on Instagram with before and after pictures with her two children, Festus and Priscilla, Iyabo Ojo wrote: “This year I began my journey as a single mum with no direction… “I was afraid, sometimes depressed, confused, i always had a lot of anxiety “I felt like a failure, a loser, i felt i wasn’t good enough, i felt little, i didn’t really know how to fit in or even start, - Advertisement - …… how was I even going to pull through,?   Feeding only thing on Nigerians’ mind, says Speed…     Whitemoney to hang out with Ojuelegba bridge co-tenants     TV actor Morgan Stevens found dead in kitchen   “I never thought of me making it in life, i just wanted my kids to be fine, that was my ultimate goal…. “All I knew to do was to love my kids immensely and give them all of me & that inspired me to keep moving..\ “Today i look back & all i want to say is thank you Lord “It’s never to late to start all over again…… it will be tough but you will be fine .. “There is always light @ the end of the tunnel.”